Executive Value Breakdown — REFUGE-P (Hard Stop)
Phase 3 (Execution License)

Audience: Executives, Program Managers, Finance, Risk

Scope Rule: This document explains where value comes from in time, money, and risk terms. It does not guarantee survival outcomes or mission success. All values are directional and comparative.

Total Internal Development Cost (Before Any Hardware Exists)

Estimated Total (Order-of-Magnitude):
High six figures to low seven figures

This estimate reflects:

concept definition

failure-mode analysis

human-factors review

legal / safety review

doctrine development

internal alignment cycles

This estimate does not include:

hardware fabrication

testing or qualification

deployment costs

launch costs

schedule slips

failed iterations

Early-phase emergency systems are disproportionately expensive because failure tolerance must be argued, not assumed.

